
# ** Format
# <type>(<optional scope>): <emoji> <subject>
# [BLANK LINE]
# <optional body>
# [BLANK LINE]
# <optional footer>
#
# ** Type
# * ğŸ“¦ build:    changes affecting build process or auxiliary tools
# * ğŸ”§ chore:    changes that don't modify src or test files
# * ğŸ‘· ci:       ci/cd related changes
# * ğŸ“š docs:     documentation only changes
# * âœ¨ feat:     a new feature
# * ğŸ› fix:      a bug fix
# * âš¡ï¸ perf:     a code change that improves performance
# * â™»ï¸ refactor: a code change that neither fixes a bug or adds a feature
# * ğŸš€ release:  create a release commit
# * âª revert:   revert previous changes
# * ğŸ¨ style:    changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (whiteÂ­space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc)
# * ğŸš¨ test:     adding missing or correcting existing tests
#
# ** Subject
# * use imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
# * no dot (.) at the end.
#
# ** Scope
# * provide additional contextual information
# * contained within parenthesis
#
# ** Body
# * use imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
# * should include the motivation for the change and contrast this with
#   previous behavior
#
# ** Footer
# * reference any tasks/tickets/issues related to this commit
# * breaking changes start with "BREAKING CHANGE:", or appends "!" after the
#   type/scope
#
# ** Additional Notes:
# * subject line 50 chars
# * body/footer 72 chars
